  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The New England Convention just closed; it was the most radical of any of the series. The iniquitous war with Mexico was discussed, with the boldest words &quot;uttered against the American government, and loyalty to it was denounced as rebellion against God.&quot; William H. Channing and Theodore Parker distinguished themselves with their doctrines. There was rejoicing at the convention over the &quot;grand meeting in Glasgow.&quot; William Lloyd Garrison hopes the Free Church (of Scotland) will return the &quot;blood-stained money&quot; to the American South. Garrison refers to an invitation to visit Scotland; he is uncertain if he can accept.</subfield>
